    "node_kind": "heading",
    "heading_text": "Response with arbitrary dict",
    "anchor_id": "response-with-arbitrary-dict",
    "section_url": "https://fastapi.tiangolo.com/tutorial/extra-models/#response-with-arbitrary-dict",
    "section_text": "You can also declare a response using a plain arbitrary dict , declaring just the type of the keys and values, without using a Pydantic model.\n\nThis is useful if you don't know the valid field/attribute names (that would be needed for a Pydantic model) beforehand.\n\nIn this case, you can use dict :",
    "section_inline_code": [
      "dict"
    ],
